headline: Want Safe Dividend Income in 2025 and Beyond? Invest in the Following 2 Ultra-High-Yield Stocks.
summary: After all, a company's ability to sustain, or even better, increase, dividends matters more.  Target (NYSE: TGT) had a challenging quarter with same-store sales (comps) increasing a tepid 0.3% for the period that ended on Nov. 2.  Undoubtedly, as price increases on basic items like food continue abating, shoppers will increase their spending dollars at Target.
